sources.description:
"Four Fast Guns" is a 1960 American Western film directed by William J. Hole Jr. and written by James Edmiston and Dallas Gaultois. 

Synopsis:
A loner (James Craig) on the lam wanders into an Old West town run by a disabled villain that no one wants to fight.

Main Cast:
James Craig as Tom Sabin
Martha Vickers as Mary Hoag
Edgar Buchanan as Dipper
Brett Halsey as Johnny Naco
Paul Richards as Hoag
Richard Martin as Quijano
